{
  "a_galaxy_workflow": "true",
  "annotation": "Phase B soft-masking, maintained-masker edition. Per strain, run four maskers over the assembly \u2014 dustmasker (DUST), windowmasker (genome-frequency), tantan (gentle LC), and fastan (tandem arrays). Each emits a content-annotated BED6 (name = repeat-unit signature / unit size, score = purity/identity, strand) that becomes a UCSC-hub track. The union of the four interval sets is soft-masked into the assembly (bedtools maskfasta -soft) and indexed (samtools faidx). Replaces the previous sdust+longdust pair (sdust unmaintained + buggy; longdust slow/redundant) per the masking-stats benchmark. Collection element identifier = strain throughout.",
  "comments": [],
  "creator": [
    {
      "class": "Person",
      "identifier": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5987-8032",
      "name": "Anton Nekrutenko"
    },
    {
      "class": "Person",
      "name": "Claude Opus 4.8"
    }
  ],
  "format-version": "0.1",
  "license": "MIT",
  "name": "WF-B softmask (Phase B) \u2014 4 maskers + BED6 + masking report",
